    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 21-SI SERIES - REASSEMBLY - BRUSHES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BRUSHES</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Individual Brushes</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801724">Figure 24</hotlnk>
                for Item numbers in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801724" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801724" filename="../figg08/g0801724.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Assembly of Brush Holder</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BRUSH</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BRUSH SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPACER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BRUSH HOLDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BRUSH CONTACT CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. BRUSH PIN</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Install brushes (Item 1), brush springs (Item 2), and spacer (Item 3) to brush holder (Item 4).
                Brushes are identical, but leads and contact clips are positioned differently. Pin brushes in retracted
                position (non-metallic pin is recommended).
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
